joke_text: Why did the data engineer break up with the database? Too many relationships!
Why did the ETL pipeline go to therapy? It had too many unresolved dependencies!
A data engineer’s favorite exercise? Cleaning up messy joins!
Why did the data engineer refuse to use Excel? Because real engineers don’t use spreadsheets, they use pipelines!
I tried to explain data lakes to my grandma, but she just told me to stop dumping data everywhere!
Data engineers don’t make mistakes… they just create ‘unexpected features’ in the pipeline!
Why do data engineers love coffee? Because without it, they’d have too many NULL pointer exceptions!
The data engineer’s motto: 'If it works, don’t touch it. If it fails, blame the schema change!'
What’s a data engineer’s favorite type of music? Heavy metadata!
Why did the data warehouse get a therapist? It had too many fact and dimension conflicts!
